        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 7:38PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 737 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sieper, or near Hineston, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lacamp, Hineston, Leander, Sieper, Clifton, Flatwoods, Gardner,
Calcasieu, Otis, Elmer, and Simpson.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 76 and 77.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
